					<description><![CDATA[I’ve picked up several different art supplies over the years, thinking that I would be able to use them for one thing or another. I picked up clay, thinking I would come up with all sorts of wonderful creations. I even imagined me making an&#160;<a class="read-more" href="https://llgt.cafe/arts-and-crafts">&#8230;</a>]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[
<p>I’ve picked up several different art supplies over the years, thinking that I would be able to use them for one thing or another.</p>



<p>I picked up clay, thinking I would come up with all sorts of wonderful creations. I even imagined me making an elephant but my creations never got beyond the imagination stage.</p>



<p>I got pencils, colored pencils and pencils that are watercolors. I even got a fancy coloring book, but I’ve hardly used any of them.</p>



<p>I got watercolors and I’ve not used them at all. It’s not that I don’t enjoy watercolors or know how to use them. I do know how to use them. It just seems that I haven’t found the occasion to use them.</p>



<p>I’ve even picked up several art pads and notebooks. One of them has been making a handy pad for my phone. But most of the art pads sit in a stack, unused and hardly touched.</p>



<p>There is one arts and craft item that I have been enjoying, and it is the least expensive of all: that is Play-Doh. I really like the texture and the smell. I don’t have to make anything special out of it and, when I’m done, I can put it right back in it’s container.</p>



<p>Sometimes, the best art supplies aren’t the fanciest or the most expensive. They say that the best camera is the one that you carry around with you. And I find Play-Doh works for me. What craft or crafts do you enjoy most? Please comment below.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
